CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1954, p. 23, reads: "GIRLS' CLUB PLANS CONFERENCE - The Junior Prep League, a teen-age organization, will entertain their mothers at a supper conference Friday, May 7, at A. Leo Weil School. "World Understanding Begins With Teen-agers" is the theme of the program. Miss Alma Boulden is chairman of the affair and Mrs. Ernestine Parks is the sponsor of the group.  Included in group are, seated, Frances Pace, Patricia White, Maxine Durham, Sandra Sales, Carol Hatton, Andrea Shepherd; behind them are Gwendolyn Martin, Lola Ruffin, Barbara Williams, Jacqueline Betty Primus, Alma Boulden, Roberta Durham, Barbara Goggins and Daryl Gloster."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fifteen girls from the Junior Prep League, including Frances Pace, Patricia White, Maxine Durham, Sandra Sales, Carol Hatton, Andrea Shepherd, Gwendolyn Martin, Lola Ruffin, Barbara Williams, Jacqueline Betty Primus, Alma Boulden, Roberta Durham, Barbara Goggins and Daryl Gloster, posed on stage, possibly at A. Leo Weil School
